(148, 79, 'Madison (Alabama)', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	Recently ranked one of the top ten cities to grow up in, Madison is a cozy and lively neighborhood. Located in the northern region of Alabama, Madison saw a Civil War battle fought on its&rsquo; land; but today it is the opposite of a war zone.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	On Saturday mornings, locals comb the bustling farmer&rsquo;s market for everything from homemade jams to artisanal cheeses, while others head to the parks for fishing, tennis, miniature golf, or soccer. Insanity Skate Parks offers batting cages and skate rinks for the more skilled athletes, but those seeking leisure might pack a picnic of goods from the market and stroll through Madison&rsquo;s antique shops or art galleries. Blue Pants Brewery and Wish You Were Beer are favorites for tasting unusual craft beers and the neighboring town of Huntsville is lined with historic museums, rocket &amp; space centers, golf clubs and restaurants galore. Still your Madison tour guide will suggest a walk along US 72 and Madison Boulevard for the town&rsquo;s best shopping and dining excursions.<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n', 1, 0, 220, '34.70', '-86.75', 'madison-alabama', 0, 1),
