(212, 83, 'Jasper', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	Jasper likes to consider itself somewhat rough around the edges; a place where real people live and the traditional ways are still kept. &nbsp;It is a very special town, and the townsfolk deserve to be proud of its unpretentiousness.&nbsp; Peace is personified here, amidst some of the world&rsquo;s most stunning wilderness, magnificent lakes and mountains.<br />\n	One is spoiled for choice with all the outdoor activities &ndash; horseback riding, hiking, camping, mountain biking, canoeing, golf, cross country skiing, ice skating and snow shoeing without covering them all.<br />\n	A Jasper tourist guide would insist on a trip to the Maligne Canyon Ice Walk.&nbsp; A summer walk is so totally different to that taken in winter; either way both are spectacular.&nbsp; Another must do is a trip on the Columbia Ice Field.&nbsp; Turquoise isn&rsquo;t a colour until it has been seen at its ultimate &ndash;glacier blue!&nbsp; The Jasper Tramway takes visitors 2,277 meters up Whistler&rsquo;s Mountain, where it&rsquo;s as if one can see forever.&nbsp; For more endless spectacular views look up at the Jasper Dark Sky; the Jasper Dark Sky festival in October proudly presents billions of twinkling stars amidst the quiet and mystery of nights at Jasper National Park!</p>\n', 1, 0, 35, '52.88', '-118.08', 'jasper', 0, 1),
