(474, 173, 'Khamis Mushayt', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	In the Asir region of Saudi Arabia lie the Saharan tribe&rsquo;s capital, Khamis Mushayt. Though the population has grown dramatically since its&rsquo; original agricultural existence, expansive farmland surrounds the city and still produces local crops of wheat and fruit. While Khamis Mushayt grows, ancient tribes continue to make up most of the residential public; streets play a soundtrack of different Arabic dialects, through which tribal customs continue to be discussed and upheld.<br />\n	Your Khamis Mushayt tour guide will explain how the regions&rsquo; ongoing indulgence in ancient traditions make for an excess of authentic shops and eateries. Souks make up a majority of shopping opportunities in Khamis Mushayt, and are comprised of streets that confusedly intertwine with colorful storefronts selling local goods. A stop at the khamis souk will find regionally made silver, while the spice souk offers the area&rsquo;s most frequently utilized seasonings and herbs. Regardless of what you dream of purchasing, the weather can play an important role in daily activities here. March and April are peak rain seasons, while year-round afternoon temperatures are often quite warm.</p>\n', 1, 0, 185, '18.31', '42.73', 'khamis-mushayt', 0, 1),
