(650, 261, 'Basel', 'Basle, Basilea, Bale', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	One of Europe&rsquo;s loveliest cities, Basel, famously located in the Dreil&auml;ndereck (three countries&#39; corner) rubs shoulders with Germany and France next door. The Rhine flows gently through, where once can enjoy a ferry ride or walk along one of the five bridges that connect one side of the city to the other.<br />\n	The Old Town of Basel is probably one of the best preserved, its cobbled alleys around the Marketplatz and the magnificent M&uuml;nster next door beckoning for a peek through history. And yet Basel is not immune to modernity, pushing the boundaries of architectural design and filling the skyline with magnificent structures.<br />\n	Clearly a city of museums covering a wide range of subjects, delve into a novel experience at the Cartoon Museum, the only museum in the world devoted to satirical art. And there&rsquo;s some fun to be had at the medieval Basler Papierm&uuml;hle, the Basel Paper Mill, where hand-made paper and books come to life.<br />\n	Basel has an air of gastronomic sophistication with many upmarket restaurants; bars and side walk cafes offering a cosmopolitan array of dishes and drinks. Your Basel tour Guide will carry listings of many strongholds of music and theatre in this culture centric city; however the real crowd spinner that doubles the city&rsquo;s population in a jiffy is the world famous Art Basel, held every June to showcase modern and contemporary art.</p>\n', 1, 0, 40, '47.57', '7.58', 'basel', 0, 1),
