(682, 275, 'Munich', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	Famous for hosting the annual Oktoberfest celebration of beer and German culture, Munich falls high on the bucket list for both wizened travellers and college-aged backpackers. This two-week festival of dancing, music, food, and of course, brews, welcomes the city&rsquo;s highest influx of tourism in early autumn. Still, Munich&rsquo;s attraction stretches far past the closing ceremonies of Oktoberfest and well into the rest of the year.<br />\n	The active nightlife and progressive music scene beats through this city&rsquo;s veins regardless of the month, while winter&rsquo;s enchanting Christmas Market light up the square with a village of holiday-inspired activities and adornments. As the Christmas tree lights fade, the city&rsquo;s active snow sport following takes over. As host of the Ski World Cup, expansive ice-skating parks and an avid curling community characterize Munich making it a lively destination regardless of weather. Beyond its&rsquo; many attractions, much of the city&rsquo;s draw lies in its&rsquo; charming ability to remain provincial and traditional amidst upscale modernization.&nbsp; Any Munich tour guide would say it is this exact contrast that makes the city an ever-satisfying tourist hotspot.</p>\n', 1, 0, 54, '48.14', '11.58', 'munich', 0, 1),
