(896, 352, 'Armstrong', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	This small rural community with a big heart is found in northern Okanagen, or Spallumcheen Valley.&nbsp; The word &ldquo;spallumcheen&rdquo; has many meanings, all along the lines of beautiful valley, flat meadow, or prairie-banked river. &nbsp;<br />\n	Ranching, logging and agriculture form the backbone of the town&rsquo;s economy.&nbsp; Long-distance cyclists are starting to use Armstrong as a stopover.&nbsp; The town also has a Stampede, dating back to 1899, which for the genteel offers contests such as sewing, cooking, and other hobbies.&nbsp; The energy of the Exhibition is found in the chuck wagon races, competitions and concerts.<br />\n	An Armstrong tourist guide would demonstrate that in such stunning landscape there is something for everyone all year round; a Museum, golf courses, fishing, boating, hiking, skiing snowmobile riding and even theatre on a farm! Armstrong has a very popular Farmers Market where local breads, cakes, jams, cheese and locally handcrafted goods are available for sale. &nbsp;</p>\n', 1, 0, 35, '50.45', '-119.18', 'armstrong', 0, 1),
