(986, 386, 'Los Angeles', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	Home to Hollywood&rsquo;s celeb-lifestyle, Rodeo Drive&rsquo;s posh, and that southern California heat, Los Angeles is a city to see and be seen. A night out downtown brings you face-to-face with some of the best-dressed people this side of New York, but a visit to its&rsquo; suburbs finds cool sports bars and charming eateries. With mild temperatures year-round and extremely limited humidity, every day can be a beach day&hellip;and most locals will tell you they usually all are. The nearby Santa Monica Pier and hippie-driven Venice Beach are SoCal staples but some time indoors must be spent visiting one of the many live television show tapings or enjoying a film studio tour- after all, it&rsquo;s still Hollywood!<br />\n	While any LA tour guide will suggest a mandatory trip through the Hollywood Walk of Fame, much of this city&rsquo;s charm lies in the air rather than specific locations. An unusual ambiance of confident swagger and laid-back friendliness fill the atmosphere, and it&rsquo;s easy for visitors to sense that famed Los Angeles flair the moment they touch down at LAX airport.&nbsp;</p>\n', 1, 0, 220, '34.11', '-118.41', 'los-angeles', 0, 1),
(987, 386, 'San Diego', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	If you&#39;ve never been to San Diego, you are missing out. A laidback beach town on California&#39;s coast, it&rsquo;s near impossible to feel anything but euphorically relaxed while in its city limits. A carefree-surfer vibe is present throughout San Diego, but the something-for-everyone neighborhoods make it a universally popular destination for singles, friends, or families. The nightlife and culinary delights boom downtown and Balboa Park boasts San Diego&rsquo;s famed zoo. Your San Diego tour guide will direct you to La Jolla for water sports, where the Pacific Ocean views offer unmatched kayaking adventures.<br />\n	Originally owned by Mexico before being obtained by the USA, San Diego&rsquo;s cuisine and culture continue to pay homage to its&rsquo; roots. In fact, it is so geographically close to Tijuana that visitors and locals alike walk across city lines to spend a day in Mexico&rsquo;s tourist town; this border crossing being one of the busiest in the world. San Diego&rsquo;s Old Town also offers visitors a theoretical step across country limits with its&rsquo; Mexico-styled shops and design, but authentic Mexican food can easily be found throughout San Diego.</p>\n', 1, 0, 220, '32.81', '-117.14', 'san-diego', 0, 1),
(988, 386, 'San Jose', '', '', 1, 0, 220, '37.30', '-121.85', 'san-jose', 0, 1),
(989, 386, 'San Francisco', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	Long a hub of literary thinkers and philosophical contrarians and once the very beating heart of California, when thousands flocked westwards in search of gold, San Francisco, with its regal Georgian townhouses, liberal politics, sprawling hillside neighbourhoods and iconic bay-side skyline (think the Golden Gate Bridge) is now one America&rsquo;s best-loved metropolises. And quite rightly so.<br />\n	First-time visitors often head straight to the heights of Telegraph Hill, where the 210-foot Coit Tower offers up sweeping panoramas of San Mateo and the Pacific bay. Others trundle across the waters to Alcatraz; a stoic reminder that this city was once the site of America&rsquo;s most notorious prison. But, whatever you do, come here with an open mind, ready to juggle the famous californian microclimates, ride the famous urban tramlines, sample the seafood on Fisherman&rsquo;s Wharf, or explore the bustling streets of Chinatown.<br />\n	For an evening adventure, be sure to quiz your San Francisco tour guide on the best downtown drinking spots or smoky beatnik speakeasies, where locals indulge in poetry readings and Californian craft ales flow from the taps. What&rsquo;s more, San Francisco is famed for its top-quality wine bars, where those with more refined palates can go to taste the best in northern Californian reds and whites.</p>\n', 1, 0, 220, '37.77', '-122.45', 'san-francisco', 0, 1),
(990, 386, 'Fresno', '', '', 1, 0, 220, '36.78', '-119.79', 'fresno', 0, 1),
(991, 386, 'Sacramento', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	Sacramento was originally put on the map after a rush of settlers in 1948 stormed the city, searching for gold. Since then, the capital of California has flourished among government buildings, the arts, and culinary strides. Centrally located between San Francisco, the California coast, and the wilderness, Sacramento offers all the amenities of a big city without the overwhelming hustle and bustle.<br />\n	Midtown is where the arts flourish, drawing locals to admire the many galleries on Second Saturdays or the Crocker Art Museum. After which, a stop in one of the many eclectic eateries is always on the menu. From comfort food to elegant sushi, the city&rsquo;s gastro opportunities do not disappoint. A good Sacramento tour guide would encourage visitors to fill their bellies and make way to one of the many attractions awaiting them. Fairytale Town appeals to the Disney Princess in all of us, the Sacramento Zoo is fun for the entire family, and historic staples like the California State Railroad Museum and Sutter&rsquo;s Fort are iconic must-sees of this capital city. Remember, the Delta breeze carries winds from the seas every day around 5 p.m.; so packing layers should always be a priority for a night out in Sacramento.&nbsp;</p>\n', 1, 0, 220, '38.57', '-121.47', 'sacramento', 0, 1),
