(1030, 386, 'Thousand Oaks', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	Known for its&rsquo; rich homes and residents, Thousand Oaks was recently rated among the top ten cities for safety and wealth. Thousand Oaks was named for its&rsquo; plentiful oak trees and the city&rsquo;s 15,000 acres of open space offers a lush escape amidst the commercial growth. Equestrians, hikers, cyclers, and runners find solace in Thousand Oaks&rsquo; many parks, especially Wildwood Regional Park. Fourteen trails, two waterfalls, three fountains, expansive greenery and massive canyons&nbsp;make Wildwood a happy escape from the bustling commerce. Located approximately 40 miles from downtown Los Angeles, Thousand Oaks offers a close connection to excitement of Hollywood without losing California&rsquo;s breathtaking countryside.<br />\n	Your Thousand Oaks tour guide would also impress on you the city&rsquo;s booming economy. Housing many technological, automobile, and financial corporations&rsquo; headquarters, such as BMW, Bank of America, and Verizon, Thousand Oaks is as industrial as it is forestry. With its&rsquo; regionally acclaimed shopping mall, this southern California city is the perfect balance of lively relaxation.&nbsp;</p>\n', 1, 0, 220, '34.19', '-118.87', 'thousand-oaks', 0, 1),
