(1103, 386, 'Union City (California)', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	Just 30 miles south of San Francisco, Union City is a suburb of the San Francisco Bay Area and lies at the northern tip of Silicon Valley. A third of the East Bay&rsquo;s &ldquo;Tri-City&rdquo; zone, Union City is accessible to all of the Bay Area&rsquo;s amenities. Three international airports, nine city bus lines and six district bus companies make Union City a convenient base to regionally and locally explore from. Plus, the Bay Area Rapid Transit delivers visitors to any of the nearby hot spots.<br />\n	Connect to the Muni Metro&rsquo;s F Line to catch a ferry to Alcatraz or take a direct trip on the Orange Line to visit Berkley&rsquo;s cultural epicenter. Visit the residential sites, San Fran&rsquo;s bustling downtown, or the streaming bay water&rsquo;s all from Union City&rsquo;s rapid transit stop. A good Union City tour guide would remind you just how much can be seen and experienced from this seemingly quiet town.</p>\n', 1, 0, 220, '37.60', '-122.02', 'union-city-california', 0, 1),
