(1167, 386, 'Dublin (California)', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	While most people hear Dublin and immediately think Ireland, this California city is just as worthy a destination. Settled in 1850 by two Irishmen, Dublin holds tight to their old country pride, boasting a weekend-long St. Patrick&rsquo;s Day festival; visitors and locals alike gather every year to pay homage to the city&rsquo;s roots with a parade, gala, pancake breakfast, and 5k run.<br />\n	Beyond its&rsquo; deep Irish heritage, the city prides itself on being a crossroads for the Bay Area and is a meeting point between the regions&rsquo; two major highways. A suburb of the San Francisco Bay Area, Dublin lies just 35 miles east of San Francisco and makes up one third of California&rsquo;s picturesque Tri-Valley. While wine-lovers head to Livermore Valley for the state&rsquo;s oldest wine region, history buffs and foodies cherish the nearby historic downtown districts of Danville and Pleasanton. With mild average temperatures of 68 degrees, the Tri-Valley area&rsquo;s beautifully manicured golf courses attract tourists year round. For many, Dublin, CA is a closer-to-home dose of Ireland and beloved weekend getaway.</p>\n', 1, 0, 220, '37.72', '-121.91', 'dublin-california', 0, 1),
