(1295, 2436, 'Ayutthaya', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	As the former royal capital of Thailand, Ayutthaya is the very essence of Thai culture. Despite having been all but destroyed by an invading army in the 1700s, the island&rsquo;s remaining legacy pays homage to the city&rsquo;s roots among its&rsquo; present-day commotion. A UNESCO listed world heritage park, palace and temples ensure Ayutthaya a prominent place of pride in Thailand&rsquo;s lengthy history; it&rsquo;s museums, cuisine, and eastern philosophies reminding tourists of just how far they&rsquo;ve travelled. The Chao Praya River, once an important conduit of trade for this city plies cruises ferrying sightseers over ambient sunsets. Meanwhile, Elephant compound provides visitors with the authentically Thai experience of living, working, and playing with elephants!<br />\n	Beyond the rich history and provincial chaos that draws tourists to this Southeast Asian island, its close proximity to Bangkok heightens its&rsquo; allure. A Ayutthaya tour guide will typically recommend a couple of days getaway as an adequately welcome escape of relaxation and authentic culture indulgence.</p>\n', 1, 0, 208, '14.36', '100.57', 'ayutthaya', 0, 1),
(1296, 2436, 'Kanchanaburi', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	Chilled-out, laid-back Kanchanaburi is a world away from the heady fray of nearby Bangkok, and a real favourite for backpackers and Thais when it comes to taking a low-energy break from the capital. It&rsquo;s also home to some of the most striking wartime memorials and points of interest in all of Southeast Asia.<br />\n	The town itself is sprawled out on the banks of the River Kwai, where the iconic steel bridge that features in the 1957 film stands reconstructed over the flow. Today, the site is home to a comprehensive museum that well chronicles the dark history of the bridge, and the thousands who died during the construction of the so-called Death Railway through Burma. Anyone interested in unravelling the story further should ask their Kanchanaburi tour guide about trips to the Hellfire Pass, or excursions to the various War Cemeteries here.<br />\n	But it&rsquo;s not all about history in &lsquo;Kanchan&rsquo; either, and visitors today enjoy a bubbling nightlife where locals meet backpackers in 10-baht roadside bars around Mae Nam Kwae Road, along with a wealth of other major attractions from the famous Tiger Temple to the seven-tiered wonder of the Erawan Falls.</p>\n', 1, 0, 208, '14.02', '99.53', 'kanchanaburi', 0, 1),
