(1371, 438, 'Chittagong', 'Chattagam', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	As the second largest city on Bangladesh, Chittagong is situated amongst thick green forests, hills that seem to roll on forever and spectacular beaches. This, and a pleasant climate have set Chittagong on its way to fast becoming a popular tourist destination. Join the avid sports fans at MA Aziz Stadium to watch a game of cricket, keeping refreshed with a green coconut water or Lassi &ndash; a yogurt drink. Housed in the Old Circuit Building, the rolling green lawns lead to The Zia Memorial Museum or spend some moments of solitude at the Bayazid Bostami Dargah Sharif shrine and the old Mosque. Whilst there, your Chittagong tour guide will point out to you the endangered Bostami Turtle who are often found walking around the pond.&nbsp; Drive through the densely populated forest to Patenga beach, which stretches right along the Bay of Bengal. Relax on the beach, take a swim, indulge in delicious street food or visit the nearby Butterfly Park. For that extra burst of energy on your holiday, visit the manmade Foy&rsquo;s Lake and hike along one of the scenic hiking trails. Reward yourself over a feast on Smoked Hilsa, Prawn Dopyaza, king prawns and lobster at one of the many local food eateries found in the city.</p>\n', 1, 0, 18, '22.33', '91.81', 'chittagong', 1, 1),
