(1469, 489, 'Denver', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	One of the Rocky Mountains&rsquo; most enticing tourist towns is Colorado&rsquo;s capital, Denver. A well-balanced city, Denver holds tights to its&rsquo; cowboy western past and sprawling mountainous backdrop, while embracing its&rsquo; role as a growing metropolis. Though its&rsquo; urbanization continues to grow among skyscrapers and bright lights, it is hard to deny the draw of the far more low key Rocky Mountains. Attracting traditional and non-traditional sporting enthusiasts, hiking, hot air ballooning, cycling, and skiing are among the many outdoor activities drawing in tourists year round.<br />\n	Any good Denver tour guide will tell you its&rsquo; downhome country roots extend far past the mountains, and right onto the city&rsquo;s dinner plates. Like much of Denver&rsquo;s personality, its&rsquo; cuisine is a well matched meeting of opposites; cozy comfort food and refined farm-to-table menus both maintain a respectful hold at local eateries. That said, when you order Denver&rsquo;s special Rocky Mountain Oysters, you will in fact be served fried bulls testicles! If that doesn&rsquo;t prove the city&rsquo;s refined equilibrium, you&rsquo;ll just have to head down to Denver and see for yourself!</p>\n', 1, 0, 220, '39.77', '-104.87', 'denver', 0, 1),
