(1684, 601, 'Durres', 'Durazzo, Enver Hoxha, Durrsi, Durresi, Dursi, Drac, Durts, Durz, Duresi', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	Enjoying great stretches of beachfront on the warm Adriatic, the city of Durres has long been one of the favoured resorts for Albanian locals in the summer. An array of waterside strips of hotels and clubs oozes with life during the warmer months, with more luxurious retreats popping up all the time.<br />\n	While Durres&rsquo; modern character and close proximity to Tirana lend it a distinct urban feel, it&rsquo;s ancient past is still unquestionably its defining feature. The city is home to a palimpsest of ancient ruins and artifacts, dating back all the way to the 7th century BC, when this small coastal peninsula was first colonised by sailors out of Greek Corinth. Of these, the most impressive is unquestionably the city&rsquo;s amphitheatre, the largest Roman structure of its kind in all of the Balkans. In addition, Durres tourist guides often recommend a walking route around the old city walls, where various medieval additions like the Tophane Well can be spotted built into bulwarks.<br />\n	What&rsquo;s more, in the early summer the Open Port Festival showcases some of the harbour town&rsquo;s most interesting historical maritime vessels, while the Durres International Film Festival in late August brings together some of the best filmmakers from the Balkans and Eastern Europe as a whole.</p>\n', 1, 0, 6, '41.33', '19.45', 'durres', 0, 1),
(1685, 602, 'Dushanbe', 'Dushambe, Dyushambe, Stalinabad, Stalinobod', '', 1, 0, 209, '38.57', '68.78', 'dushanbe', 0, 1),
(1686, 603, 'Danang', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	Located halfway up the coastal spine of Vietnam, the bubbling city of Danang is something of a microcosm of the country&rsquo;s touristic experience, offering a crossroads of pearly white beaches, high rise hotels, luxurious resort complexes and curious cultural treats. This makes it the perfect stopover for those making their way through the central heartlands of the country, and a great place to enjoy classic Vietnamese city life away from the seething intensity of the capitals.<br />\n	Most Danang tourist guides will recommend a trip to the curious Marble Mountain monoliths that pierce the skyline around nine kilometres from the centre of town. Here, it&rsquo;s possible to climb the winding stairs of Thuy Son, where the various Hindu and Buddhist religious sites that cling to the peaks can be observed.<br />\n	For sunbathers, swimmers and wind surfers, the magnificent curve of China Beach will be the perfect out-of-town trip. It lies just to the east of town and is home to many of Danang&rsquo;s most laid-back bars and backpacker haunts. Elsewhere, the inner-city nightlife is fast becoming one of the best in the country, boasting a number of super clubs and plenty of those quintessential Southeast Asian bamboo bars, where beer and cocktails flow into the night.</p>\n', 1, 0, 228, '16.07', '108.21', 'danang', 0, 1),
(1687, 603, 'Nha Trang', 'Nhatrang', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	The coastal town of Nha Trang, Vietnam offers visitors views of some of the prettiest white beaches and clear blue waters that are home to a very diverse population of coral life. This is the perfect ambience for a wide array of water sports such as sailing, rafting, snorkeling or exploring the beautiful underwater world with diving. The sweet rusticity of the farms, villages and jungles around can be explored by availing a biking or motorcycle tour. Complement the trip with a dip at the Ba Ho waterfall or a relaxing massage and mud bath at the Thap Ba Hot Springs and Mud Baths. Nha Trang tourist guides would recommend a visit to Long Son Pagoda as a must see for visitors in addition to the Po Nagar Cham Towers. Another avenue for exploration in the city is via the culinary route. Food for all budgets and all varieties from Vietnamese street food to western cuisines with an accent on seafood is readily available and more of that not delicious.&nbsp; Go to Nha Trang, to uncover what the French did many years ago; a charming coastal town blessed with one of the most breathtaking bays in the world!</p>\n', 1, 0, 228, '12.25', '109.19', 'nha-trang', 0, 1),
