(1691, 603, 'Tam Ky', '', '', 1, 0, 228, '15.57', '108.49', 'tam-ky', 0, 1),
(1692, 603, 'Hoi An', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	The ancient town of Hoi An dating way back to the 15<sup>th</sup> century, is an incredibly well-preserved example of a typical South East Asian trading port. Considered one of the only towns in Vietnam to have survived the turmoil of the country&rsquo;s past, Hoi An is a fascinating piece of living history, thus awarded the accolade of a UNESCO world heritage site.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	Once the principal port of the Cham kingdom, the people of Hoi An now comprise a mix of mostly Hindu, Chinese and Vietnamese creating an area alive with diversity. Tourists are well catered for; contact a Hoi An tourist guide and purchase just one ticket to gain access to five of the many attractions the quaint old town has to offer, including a museum, an old house, a craft workshop, the traditional theatre and either the Quan Cng Temple or the Japanese covered bridge.&nbsp;</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	Relatively inexpensive compared to many tourist destinations in the east, go all out and sample the fine cuisine and impressive shopping opportunities in this charming Vietnamese port town. &nbsp;</p>\n', 1, 0, 228, '15.88', '108.34', 'hoi-an', 0, 1),
(1693, 604, 'Duzce', '', '', 1, 0, 214, '40.85', '31.15', 'duzce', 0, 1);
