(1779, 627, 'London', 'Llundain, Londres', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	The city of London is not so much one harmonious metropolis as a curious conglomeration of districts, communities, cultures, creeds, religious faiths and various inner-city centres that converge to create a mass of touristic interest, one that would require time ad infinitum to explore with all the attention it really deserves.<br />\n	Most London tour guides will point first-timers to the beating central heart of the city, to the green swathes of Hyde Park and Kensington, or the iconic gothic complex of Westminster Palace and the Norman style Tower of London. But London is a city hard to tame, and these most ubiquitous sights in isolation will do its bursting kaleidoscope of cultural hotspots, galleries, museums, historical &lsquo;must sees&rsquo; and quirky hipster neighbourhoods very little justice.<br />\n	For these, think about enlisting the help of an expert London tourist guide, who can aid in unravelling the mysterious underbelly of this city&rsquo;s various sprawling urban centres, from the bohemian bars of Camden and the Eastside, to the Georgian residential districts of Chelsea and the Thames River Embankment.</p>\n', 1, 0, 74, '51.52', '-0.10', 'london', 0, 1),
(1780, 627, 'Birmingham', '', '', 1, 0, 74, '52.48', '-1.91', 'birmingham', 0, 1),
(1781, 627, 'Liverpool', 'Lerpwl', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	Once the stomping ground of The Beatles and Frankie Goes to Hollywood, Liverpool does well to live up to its reputation for cultural excellence, spouting footballing greats, musical luminaries, poets and politicians to boot. What&rsquo;s more, the locals are among the earthiest, funniest and friendliest in the United Kingdom, touting stout ales and a homely northern attitude to match.<br />\n	When it comes to sightseeing and activities, this city has such a mishmash of various hotspots that it can be difficult to know precisely where to begin. Be sure to ask your Liverpool tourist guide for tips on the major musts; perhaps the Gothic Victoria Gallery, or the amazing Merseyside Maritime Museum on the docks. Then there are the glorious Victorian buildings of the downtown to see, and the terraces of Anfield Stadium to explore&mdash;echoing forever with the fervent choruses of You&rsquo;ll Never Walk Alone.<br />\n	After dark, Liverpool transforms once again, with clubs up and down Seel Street beating to the timeless tunes of The Beatles, and pulsating pubs hosting such an eclectic array of live music, it could only have come from streets of multicultural Liverpool.</p>\n', 1, 0, 74, '53.42', '-2.99', 'liverpool', 0, 1),
