(2023, 661, 'Palm Beach Gardens', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	Palm Beach Gardens, Florida is a top golfer&rsquo;s destination and even houses the Professional Golfer&rsquo;s Association of America&rsquo;s headquarters. With the most esteemed golfing corporation looking over their shoulder, this city&rsquo;s courses are perfectly manicured and often privately owned, but most hotels assist visitors in finding a place to play. Such is the esteemed level of golfing in Palm Beach Gardens that it has long since been used as the ultimate winter getaway for high profile families, like the Trumps and Kennedys.<br />\n	Still, your knowledgeable Palm Beach Gardens tour guide would advise you to spend time off the green as well. Like most of Florida&rsquo;s Atlantic Coast, the beaches overflow with water sports, sailing, sunbathers, and the boat-only Intracoastal Highway. If the sun becomes too strong and you need a day away, Downtown at the Gardens invites visitors to meander their landscaped sidewalks and park-like fountains at this pedestrian-only exposition of boutiques, restaurants, and an enchanting wooden carousel.</p>\n', 1, 0, 220, '26.84', '-80.12', 'palm-beach-gardens', 0, 1),
