(2034, 661, 'Fort Pierce', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	If scuba diving, snorkeling or fishing makes your eager heart skip a beat, book a trip to Fort Pierce today! Nestled on Florida&rsquo;s Atlantic Coast, Fort Pierce&rsquo;s colorful reefs and richly inhabited lagoon gives visitors an up-close look at life beneath the ocean&rsquo;s surface.&nbsp; The Indian River Lagoon boats 4,000 species of plants and animals, and boat tours guide cheering visitors through the waterway for dolphin and manatee sightings. A day of such excitement calls for another of total relaxation, and Fort Pierce&rsquo;s ample beaches and nearby winery is the perfect supplier.<br />\n	Your Fort Pierce tour guide will highlight that the city is far more than just another beach town. A 1920s-era theater and City Hall building offer a charming vintage ambience, but the emphasis on wildlife is really what distinguishes Fort Pierce from its&rsquo; neighboring coastal towns. The city&rsquo;s botanical garden, aquarium, and Manatee observation center are home to animals and plants from around the world. With its&rsquo; high quality aquatic tours and inland observatories, Fort Pierce offers a unique insight to wildlife, local and foreign.</p>\n', 1, 0, 220, '27.44', '-80.32', 'fort-pierce', 0, 1),
