(2361, 790, 'Panipat', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	The small ancient city of Panipat has been pivotal to the control of Northern India on three occasions; three major battles have been fought here in the past and all have led to the victor taking control of the fertile Gangetic Plains beyond the city. The city&rsquo;s historical significance does not stop there, having been mentioned in the ancient Indian epic, the Mahabharata.<br />\n	Keeping with the historical context, your Panipat tour guide will take you on a tour of the battlefields to visit the monuments and tombs that stand as a remembrance to the victors and the vanquished. Don&rsquo;t miss out on the outstanding Panipat Museum with it&#39;s many artifacts and antiquities and the tomb of the great Urdu poet and Sufi Saint Bu-Ali Shah Kalandar which draws followers from all faiths to offer prayers. &nbsp;A visit to Panipat will provide a deep insight into how important this small city has been significant in shaping the history of India.</p>\n', 1, 0, 100, '29.39', '76.96', 'panipat', 0, 1),
