(2565, 862, 'Paris', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	Unarguably one of the most romantic cities in the world, Paris exudes a sense of history, charm and sophistication. The best way to get into the Paris vibe is to let your Paris Tourist Guide lead you on a walking tour of the city. The imposing Eiffel Tower promises panoramic views of high-rise buildings, palaces, monuments and ancient trees. Famous for the Hunchback of Notre Dame, the Cathedral of Notre- Dame with its arresting gothic style architecture and magnificent stained glass windows is home to numerous spiritual concerts and events. Brimming with art and culture, Paris offers a veritable choice, ranging from the Louvre and its collections of remarkable art pieces to an evening of risqu&eacute; entertainment at the Moulin Rouge.&nbsp; Uniqueness and talent further bring to mind the village of Montmartre, its cobbled streets beckoning curious travellers to explore. &nbsp;Walk through the Arc de Triomph to the Avenue des Champs-Elysees where the best of Paris haute couture can be bought. A stroll along the magical river Seine would be the perfect way to whet your appetite; many delightful cafes with delicate pastries, restaurants offering nouvelle cuisine and bistros with home cooked food offer one a wide choice of food both day and night. &nbsp;</p>\n', 1, 0, 72, '48.86', '2.34', 'paris', 0, 1),
