(2716, 910, 'Surabaya', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	Indonesia&rsquo;s second largest metropolis, Surabaya&rsquo;s central role in the country&rsquo;s political development during the 20<sup>th</sup> century is eulogised by its commanding epithet: &ldquo;The city of Heroes.&rdquo; Today, it is one of the prime stop-off points on the overland route to Bali, and a great launch pad for travellers looking to make the hike up Mount Bromo in the Tengger Semeru to the south.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	Surabaya tour guides will fill you in on it&rsquo;s local legend that the city stands on the site where two of Indonesia&rsquo;s mightiest animals fought it out for dominion of the region. The city&rsquo;s lengthy history dates right back to the first half of the 13<sup>th</sup> century, during which it has undergone colonial rule and taken centre stage in Indonesia&rsquo;s national bid for independence during the 1940s. Consequently the downtown is now peppered with architectural remnants of a bygone age, like the magnificent European-influenced Gereja Kelahiran Santa Perawan Maria Chruch, and the post-colonial complexes at Sampoerna.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	The city, ever since has shouldered its way to the forefront of Indonesia&rsquo;s commercial modernity, and the glistening developments of the CBD stand as a symbol of the town&rsquo;s relative wealth. &nbsp;Any visitor to Surabaya can hence look forward to a town at once both modern and ancient, oozing with history and ready to impress.&nbsp;</p>\n', 1, 0, 96, '-7.24', '112.74', 'surabaya', 0, 1),
(2717, 910, 'Malang', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	Once the regal seat of the Kanjuruhan and Singhasari kings, Malang in East Java remains one of Indonesia&rsquo;s most intriguing historical centres; a place where the more modern images of Dutch colonialism still linger on in the shadow of centuries-old temples.<br />\n	The city of today has an energetic vibe lurking about its leafy boulevards. Perhaps it&rsquo;s the students who come here from right across the country, or the rising visitor population in search of the much-photographed Balekambang Beach, the strong coffee, breath-taking jungle surroundings, sprawling night markets and altogether enthralling ambience Malang cannot help but exude.<br />\n	But beaches, temples and local life aside, Malang tourist guides will also be quick to tout the city&rsquo;s culinary prowess; the succulent ayam goreng kampong chicken; the ubiquitous street-side jagung bakar; the meaty bakso malang soup. Then there are the museums, or the possible excursions to Sempu Island&mdash;one of the most beautiful off all of Java as a whole.&nbsp;</p>\n', 1, 0, 96, '-7.98', '112.62', 'malang', 0, 1),
