(3103, 1083, 'Preah Sihanouk', 'Preah Seihanu, Sihanoukville, Kompong Som', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	Famed for the starkly contrasting accolades of being bordered on three sides by pristine tropical beaches and being the last official US army battleground in the Vietnam War, Preah Sihanouk is a charming sea port in the province of Sihanoukville in Cambodia.<br />\n	Located on the Gulf of Thailand, Preah Sihanouk is home to some of the most beautiful beaches Cambodia has offer. Sporting names like Victory, Serendipity and Independence Beach, it&rsquo;s clear the people of Preah Sihanouk are proud of their glistening shoreline. Take time off the beach sprawl to visit the Song Saa-Khmer islands in the virginal Koh Rong Archipelago. The breath-taking coral reefs and variety of marine life here attract divers, snorkelers and game fishing enthusiasts from all over the globe. &nbsp;Another must-see in every Preah Sihanouk travel guide is the Ream National Park and surrounding waterfalls, located just half an hour away from the town centre.<br />\n	Beach-Life is thirsty work, but luckily you&rsquo;ll always be able to access a cool beer in Preah Sihanouk, as it is also home to Cambodia&#39;s national beer,&nbsp;Angkor Beer.</p>\n', 1, 0, 111, '10.61', '103.53', 'preah-sihanouk', 0, 1),
(3104, 1084, 'Vaxjo', '', '', 1, 0, 189, '56.88', '14.80', 'vaxjo', 0, 1),
(3105, 1085, 'Kruje', 'Croia', '<p class="fr-tag" style="text-align: justify;">Rising from between the treetops of the mountain that shares its name, the city of Kruje is a curious palimpsest of historical architecture, shaped by the forming hands of Illyrian tribespeople, Albanian monarchies and Ottoman imperialists alike. </p><p class="fr-tag" style="text-align: justify;">Today, the town attracts masses of day-trippers from the country’s capital at Tirana, promising sweeping views of central Albania, the rugged hills of the Ishem River basin, and the breathtaking Adriatic coast in the distance. Other travellers come to seek out trinkets in the dusty Ottoman Bazaar, where reams of handcrafted woodworks, carpets and jewellery adorn the emporiums. Having done that, many choose to visit to the National Ethnographic Museum of Kruje.</p><p class="fr-tag" style="text-align: justify;">As any Kruje tour guide will tell you, this town is primarily known to locals as the birthplace of George Kastrioti Skanderbeg, a 15<sup>th</sup>-century Albanian nobleman renowned for his military acumen. Sprawling exhibitions dedicated to the national hero can be found inside Kruje Castle and the Skanderbeg Museum, not to mention a smattering of monuments that are peppered throughout the town.</p>', 1, 0, 6, '41.52', '19.80', 'kruje', 0, 1),
