(3151, 1108, 'Kyoto', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	The intricate cityscape of old Japan and lively bustle as a modern metropolis make no two days in Kyoto alike. One day&rsquo;s walk might lead you pass an elaborate temple, while a turn the next day will treat you to shopping sprees at a trendy clothing boutique. As if its&rsquo; mix of old and new haven&rsquo;t already created a city of endless exploration, Kyoto&rsquo;s culture and make-up changes along with the season; everything from the bakery&rsquo;s sweets to geisha&rsquo;s wigs reflect the shifting weather.<br />\n	Any good Kyoto tour guide will note there&rsquo;s no better way to see the ever-changing physicality than via bicycle, as the city&rsquo;s bike paths are extremely user-friendly. If two-wheels seems unappealing, Kyoto&rsquo;s advanced public transportation system makes getting around easy- just make sure you get around. Whether you opt for a hiking excursion in the surrounding mountains, pursue a flower arranging class with a local Kado specialist, or enjoy a traditional tea ceremony, engulf yourself in this soothing and enticing city&rsquo;s culture for an unforgettable travel experience.&nbsp;</p>\n', 1, 0, 108, '35.01', '135.75', 'kyoto', 0, 1),
