(3320, 1180, 'New Orleans', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	New Orleans is a city like none other and a traveller&rsquo;s dream. Located in Louisiana, a creole-Cajun spice runs through the city&rsquo;s veins, infiltrating its&rsquo; food, people, history and nightlife, while its&rsquo; French roots give this destination a charming and unique architectural appearance. It&rsquo;s wild party scene, Dixieland jazz, culinary conquests and mysterious voodoo culture has made New Orleans a sound success for families, couples, and singles.<br />\n	Tourists eager to let loose hurdle to Bourbon Street for the rowdiest party scene at Mardi Gras, while a quieter ambience can be found in some of the world&rsquo;s best Jazz clubs. A nighttime walk through its&rsquo; haunted ceremonies or visit to a voodoo temple offers a scarier thrill, and New Orleans&rsquo; historic French Quarter houses the city&rsquo;s classic restaurants, music venues, and shops. Regardless of the path you choose to walk, there&rsquo;s a New Orleans tour guide to lead you. Known for its&rsquo; welcoming tourism office and many multifarious tour options, there&rsquo;s no reason not to plan your next trip to New Orleans.&nbsp;</p>\n', 1, 0, 220, '30.07', '-89.93', 'new-orleans', 0, 1),
