(3367, 1199, 'Maan', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	Ma&rsquo;an has long been the kingpin and gateway to historical Jordan. The capital city of the Ma&rsquo;an governorate has been the jump off point for explorers looking to take in the ubiquitous wonders of the ancient city of Petra located just 30 kilometres northward. And it&rsquo;s historical wealth doesn&rsquo;t end there, because it&rsquo;s been perched on the confluence of Middle Eastern trade routes since its foundation in the 4th century BC, helping it to accumulate a curious plethora of cultural influences from right across the Arabian Peninsula.<br />\n	The Ma&rsquo;an of today is home to the country&rsquo;s prestigious King Ḥussein University, giving it a youthful and diversified vibe. Yet, the town simmers amidst a state of unrest; a challenging situation for the well-developed collection of Ma&rsquo;an tour guides, each offering a variety of excursions into the deserts and historic sites of the greater Ma&rsquo;an province, from exploring the ruins of Petra to cruising through the rusty red canyons around town on a camel.</p>\n', 1, 0, 107, '30.19', '35.73', 'maan', 0, 1),
