(3515, 1252, 'Maputo', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	Mozambique&rsquo;s capital city and most important harbour, Maputo is among Africa&rsquo;s more attractive cities. Spreading out from the port, the heart of the city is amongst its colonial-style Portuguese buildings where locals enjoy the twin pursuits of trade and leisure out in the sun. Buildings of that time like the Railway Station and the Iron House are good for a city tour, but for an authentic experience undertake a tour with your Maputo tour guide in the multicultural neighbourhood of Mafalala. The epic Municipal Market, famous for its seafood also gives one a spicy taste of the bustling local culture and cuisine while the Avenida Julius Nyerere is a fantastic spot for shopping. The museums of Maputo are not to be missed especially the Nucleo de Arte, home to over 100 Mozambique artists and open to visitors for workshops and exhibitions.<br />\n	The pace slows somewhat at the Elephant Reserve and even more along the seaside at the beaches of Catembe and Ponta d&#39;Ouro. The beautiful Inhaca Island nearby is the perfect spot relax over Mozambican beer and a fresh meal of peri peri prawns.</p>\n', 1, 0, 152, '-25.95', '32.57', 'maputo', 0, 1),
