(4284, 1495, 'Belfast', 'Béal Feirste', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	The energetic Irish city of Belfast clearly has a lot to offer; award winning restaurants and boisterous pubs, shopping, a thriving nightlife and friendly residents. And then there are the sights to see; with a choice of bus, taxi or walking tours, exploring this sprawling city with a Belfast tour guide makes for a fantastic experience.<br />\n	The city is a combination of Edwardian and modern architecture surrounded by mountains and beautified by vast tracts of green gardens and parks, the two styles inexplicably complementing one another. For history aficionados, the City Hall and lovely churches beckon, or if you are interested in natural sciences, a visit to the Ulster Museum is free. Join the ice hockey fans to watch the Belfast Giants at the Odyssey Arena and catch a view of the city&rsquo;s rooftops from the top of the Dome. Rich in maritime history, the exhibitions at the Thompson Dock and Pump House relate the story of building the famous ship, the Titanic.<br />\n	Relax at St George&rsquo;s Market with a cup of coffee and a tasty home-made dishes whilst listening to one of the music ensembles gently providing background music and you are truly at home in Belfast.</p>\n', 1, 0, 74, '54.60', '-5.93', 'belfast', 0, 1),
