(4401, 1525, 'Maun', 'Boteti, Botetle', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	As one of Botswana`s most important tourist centers, Maun is the main gateway to the Okavango Delta, and it`s spread along the Thamalakane River. You can visit places like the Nhabe Museum, the Crocodile Farm, or the Maun Environmental Education Center if you find yourself in this area.&nbsp; However if you`re looking for a more exciting and adventurous experience you could go on a wild safari, or if you prefer to sightsee from distance, you can take a helicopter ride over this beautiful city. When it comes to the nightlife, the Power Station is the spot to go to thanks to the variety of bars and restaurants that can be found here, but during the day, Tsodilo Hills and the Makgadikgadi Pans are an excellent choice for any tourist to visit. As any Maun tourist guide will tell you, this lovely town is the perfect mix between natural and raw landscape, fascinating wildlife, and modern buildings!</p>\n', 1, 0, 32, '-19.99', '23.42', 'maun', 0, 1),
