(4427, 1535, 'Toronto', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	Toronto embraces ethnicity and diversity with grace, a testament to Canada&rsquo;s multicultural ethos.&nbsp; This fabulous city has so much to offer all year round; Toronto Tour guides are never short of places to show and tell.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	The largest city in Canada and capital of Ontario, Toronto has Lake Ontario at its feet. The many well-groomed parks contribute towards the beauty and orderliness of the city.&nbsp; Look out for concerts in the park in the summers.&nbsp; Cycling is encouraged in Toronto and cycle lanes throughout the city ensure the safety of cyclists.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	Be part of a baseball game at the impressive Skydome, an architectural marvel where the roof closes like the wings of a bug.&nbsp; Speaking of architecture, one cannot but catch the CN Tower, the second highest freestanding building in the world.&nbsp;</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	Performing arts is well established in the city with dance and ballet companies, symphony orchestras, and many theatres.&nbsp; There are museums for all tastes, book fares, and restaurants reflecting the ethnicity of the city.&nbsp;</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	Canadians love their trees and autumn, with an explosion of gold, red, yellow and orange as trees prepare for the hard winter ahead is not to be missed. Eaton Square and Kensington Street beckon for retail therapy; but the Path, the largest underground shopping complex in Toronto, effectively serves multiple purposes with 29km of shopping arcades, linking sports and cultural events, public transport and offices.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	You will fall in love with Toronto, one of the most beautiful cities in the world. &nbsp;</p>\n', 1, 0, 35, '43.65', '-79.38', 'toronto', 0, 1),
(4428, 1535, 'Ottawa', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	Charming Ottawa is a smooth cocktail of a touristic adventure. It&rsquo;s made strong by a long historical narrative of river-dwelling aboriginals and British colonialism, easy-to-savour by its laid-back locals and discernable by its pretty downtown visage, loaded with the smooth-cut architecture of Gatineau and the glorious majesty of Parliament Hill.<br />\n	The capital city is built around the Rideau Canal, a UNESCO World Heritage Site that becomes even more alluring in winters when it converts into the world&rsquo;s longest (8 km) skating rink. Sightseeing opportunities abound, and those visiting at a time when the elements allow for city strolls should be sure to quiz their Ottawa tourist guide about the must see buildings of the downtown&mdash;from the Victorian Gothic Houses of Commons, to the beautiful Library of Parliament. Then there are the fantastic institutions; the Bytown Museum of Ottowa&rsquo;s own history and the massive Canadian Museum of Civilization, both definitely worth the visit (even if you do miss the free-admission parties on Canada Day).<br />\n	Foodies will adore this metropolis too, its evidence of cultural diversity exhibited through all those hole-in-wall joints serving steaming noodles in Chinatown, those Italian pastry houses dousing beavertail breads in oodles of cinnamon, and that heady overload of classic Canadian coffeehouses.</p>\n', 1, 0, 35, '45.42', '-75.71', 'ottawa', 0, 1),
(4429, 1535, 'Hamilton', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	Hamilton is a port city on the edge of the Greater Toronto Area, situated on Lake Ontario.&nbsp; Sixty percent of Canada&rsquo;s steel is produced in Hamilton, hence its sobriquet as the &ldquo;Steel Capital of Canada&rdquo;.&nbsp; Industrial output aside, the city is fast gaining fame for its burgeoning arts scene and excellent quality of life.<br />\n	The Niagara Escarpment runs through the middle of the city, bisecting the city into upper and lower areas. The 885km Bruce Trail runs the length of the escarpment, from Niagara Falls, through Hamilton and up to Tobermorey.&nbsp; Hamilton is a big city with a country feeling and surprisingly has more than 100 waterfalls and cascades. The escarpment creates its own milder climate, thus conducive to fruit growing, the produce being available aplenty at Farmers Markets in the city.<br />\n	There are many museums and memorials in Hamilton including the Canadian Warplane Heritage Museum, the Museum of Steel and Technology, and the Canadian Football Hall of Fame.&nbsp; Your Hamilton Tour Guide may spook you into signing up for the popular Haunted Hamilton Ghost Walks for&nbsp; a supernatural experience in the city.&nbsp;</p>\n', 1, 0, 35, '43.26', '-79.85', 'hamilton', 0, 1),
