(4454, 1535, 'Midland', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	Jutting out into the waters of Lake Huron, the picturesque town of Midland is one of the premier holidaying spots on all of Georgian Bay. In the summer it swells with visitors looking to explore the wetlands of Wye Marsh and the dense second-growth forests of the nearby Awenda Provincial Park, while in the winter it becomes a haven for ice fishing, Nordic skiing and backcountry snowmobiling.<br />\n	Those looking to enjoy the full blast of the Ontario countryside that&rsquo;s offered here may want to head out to nearby Penetanguishene, with its old forts and island hopping opportunities. Others will want to explore the rolling fields around Tiny and Tay, or the rugged coastal spots of Nottawasaga Bay.<br />\n	But amidst the obvious outdoorsy pursuits here there are also historic points of interest to boot, from the downtown Martyr&#39;s Shrine, to the recreated Sainte-Marie among the Hurons, the first Catholic missionary in all of Ontario. Oh, and be sure to ask your Midland tour guide about those eye-catching murals adorning the walls all around town!</p>\n', 1, 0, 35, '44.75', '-79.89', 'midland', 0, 1),
