(4669, 1562, 'Queenstown', '', '<p  justify;">\n Long the adrenaline mecca of New Zealand (and arguably the world!) as a whole, Queenstown booms forth from rugged Otago in a breath-taking array of glacial mountain peaks, shimmering lakes, roaring river ways and glistening ski fields.<br />\n The looming summits of the rugged Southern Alps cast their ever-present silhouettes over this pretty waterside town on the banks of azure Wakatipu. Together, they stand as a reminder of Queenstown&rsquo;s indelible connection to nature, throwing up the pistes of the Remarkables and Treble Cone, whitewater rafting opportunities, the hiking routes of the legendary Queenstown Trail, oodles of mountain biking tracks and fly fishing spots along the way. And if you really want to get the blood flowing, there are always those high-speed jet boats down the Shotover River, the iconic bungee spot of the Kawarau Bridge, or tandem skydives over the picturesque town<br />\n Queenstown tour guides also offer some more relaxing pursuits in this charming outdoors resort. There are the movie location tours, scenic flights departing daily over the Milford Sound, local crafts shopping in the town centre and plenty of wine cellars touting Otago whites and reds.</p>\n', 1, 0, 164, '-45.04', '168.64', 'queenstown', 0, 1),
(4670, 1562, 'Wanaka', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	Adrenaline seekers and lovers of the outdoors assemble, because Wanaka is one of New Zealand&rsquo;s most up-and-coming adventure travel destinations. And why not, it&rsquo;s got everything you&rsquo;d expect; the snow-tipped peaks of the Crown Range and the Southern Alps all around; the great swathes of emerald-blue water that constitute Lake Wanaka; the rugged backcountry of Otago&rsquo;s Mount Aspiring National Park; the meandering stretch of the Matukituki River.<br />\n	Such surroundings are what have given Wanaka its incumbent wealth of adventure tour operators today, offering guests everything from fly fishing excursions, to skydiving above the mountains. If that&rsquo;s got you excited then be sure to ask your Wanaka tourist guide for their recommendations on the best outfitters in town.<br />\n	What&rsquo;s more, in the winter, Wanaka transforms into one of the most-visited destinations in South Island, offering guests easy access to the nearby ski fields of Treble Cone and the soaring Cardrona, not to mention a ticket to some of the wildest New Year&rsquo;s parties in the country!</p>\n', 1, 0, 164, '-44.70', '169.15', 'wanaka', 0, 1),
