(5088, 1682, 'Cancun', '', '<p class="fr-tag">Thoughts of a beach holiday typically conjure up visions of white sand beaches and deep blue seas. Such dreams do come true at Cancun, a paradisiacal Mexican city charmingly anchored by the Caribbean Sea. </p><p class="fr-tag">Recognised by the World Tourism Organization as an advanced tourism platform, Cancun has everything a tourist looking for a fun n beach holiday can wish for: an enigmatic and beautiful island across a narrow portion of the incredible Caribbean sea, the most luxurious hotels with their own private beaches, a port brimming with pubs and restaurants serving fresh sea food and live music, adventure tourism activities (read snorkeling and scuba diving in the reefs among many others), aquariums, modern water amusement parks and even an Underwater museum off the coast of Isla de Mujeres </p><p class="fr-tag">For those looking for an initiation into the local culture, the Mayan Legacy just next door is waiting to be explored. Ask your Cancun Tour guide to lead the way to the historic sites of Chichen Itza, Tulum and Coba city built by the Mayan civilization. This historical area gives those who visit, a great appreciation for the ingenious building practices of the Mayan civilization.</p>', 1, 0, 150, '21.16', '-86.85', 'cancun', 0, 1),
(5089, 1682, 'Playa del Carmen', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	It&rsquo;s telling that locals here refer to this golden stretch of coral-white sands and turquoise shore waters as simply &lsquo;Playa&rsquo;, as if it&rsquo;s the quintessential beachfront for them too. But there&rsquo;s also much more to this stylish little hotspot in the midst of the Mayan Riviera than just sun-kissed sands and reef-laden seas; there the hip boutiques of the Quinta Avenida; the European trattorias; the thriving all-inclusive resorts.<br />\n	In-between the ubiquitous days of beachcombing and sunbathing, snorkelling and diving enthusiasts can look forward to a range of unique experiences here, navigating one of the many cenotes that dot the Yucatan peninsula or exploring the rich natural aquariums of XelHa. A wealth of worthy attractions all around awaits visitors too; from the soaring cliff top Mayan ruins at Tulum, to the unique biosphere reserves of Sian Ka&#39;an and Rio Lagartos.<br />\n	For the evenings, be sure to quiz your Playa del Carmen tour guide on the best gastronomy in town, and don&rsquo;t leave without sampling the spicy seafood tacos, or dancing the night away in one of the suave clubs that are slowly creeping their way down the coast from nearby Cancun.</p>\n', 1, 0, 150, '20.63', '-87.08', 'playa-del-carmen', 0, 1),
