(5385, 1111, 'Riohacha', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	The Columbian city of Riohacha was founded in 1535, when colonial Europeans flocked to the area upon the discovery of pearls.<br />\n	Historically, Riohacha was an important port during colonization and independence. The city is firmly entrenched in the Columbian tourism map as a gateway to the sights of La Guajira; recent inputs into tourism however highlight that there is so much more the city can showcase. Your Riohacha tour guide will highly recommend a tour of the Wildlife Sanctuary Los Flamencos. Pack a picnic to enjoy the stunning beaches of Cabo de la Vela, arguably one of the most beautiful in Columbia.&nbsp; Punta Gallinas packs in azure blue seas, mangroves and dunes rippling into the sea. Follow the author Gabriel Garcia Marquez&rsquo;s settings for Cien A&ntilde;os de Soledad by touring the peninsula of La Guajira. Walk by the Paseo de La Marina to see the beautiful handicrafts of the Wayuu community or simply sit back and enjoy a sunset over the lovely beaches of Riohacha.</p>\n', 1, 0, 46, '11.54', '-72.91', 'riohacha', 0, 1),
