(5578, 1858, 'Gori', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	Gori, is located 47 miles west of Georgia`s capital, Tbilisi, at the confluence of the Mtkvari and Greater Liakhvi rivers. The town is known most notably as the birthplace of Joseph Stalin and, further back in time, its tumultuous history as a military stronghold in the Middle Ages. It. A statue of Stalin was present in front of the Town Hall, until it was removed in 2010 to signify a withdrawal from the Soviet influence. Sweeping views of the modern city that Gori has transformed into today can be caught from the Gori Fortress, built atop a hill at the centre of the city.&nbsp; Hike up yet another hill to discover the St. George`s church of Gori Jvari, a place of pilgrimage worshipped by the locals even today. A bit away is Uplistsikhe, once a bustling cave city over 3000 years ago. It would be advisable to engage a Gori tour guide to have a better understanding of this ancient city especially the amphitheater the church and what one would believe to be the pharmacy at that time!&nbsp; &nbsp;Do keep some time in hand to visit other places in Gori, such as the Joseph Stalin Museum, or the former Georgian Agrarian Science Academy Branch, now known as Sukhishvili University.</p>\n', 1, 0, 76, '41.98', '44.11', 'gori', 0, 1),
