(5906, 1997, 'Tanga', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	Tanga is a lovely coastal city with a diversity of attractions in addition to its magnificent beaches. A must do in any travel itinerary around Tanga would include a visit to the Amboni caves, beautiful limestone caves that hold religious significance for the local tribes as evidenced from the artifacts and pottery found in its chambers. Hot on the sightseeing trail, Tongoni ruins is where you go to see 15<sup>th</sup> century ruins of a mosque and tombs. Choose from many boating excursions to the nearby islands such as Yambie Island or Sandbank Island for fishing trips or a sailing excursion. Don&rsquo;t miss listening to the myths and stories surrounding the majestic Baobab trees at Toten Island. Pop over with your Tanga tour guide to a village to consult a traditional healer, participate in a Swahili dance or, better still learn how the local brew is prepared. . The cosmopolitan amenities of shopping, varied dining options and an entertaining nightlife are easily available around the city. However, to be one with nature, take that camping trip or, simply have a date with serenity at the Mwarongo sandy beaches.</p>\n', 1, 0, 217, '-5.07', '39.09', 'tanga', 0, 1),
