(5998, 2032, 'Chattanooga', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	Rich in history, Chattanooga tells a story of past Civil War battles and Trail of Tears beginnings. Its&rsquo; calculated position near major river ways and rail systems made the city a gateway to the Deep South, and a common site for Confederate and Union soldiers&rsquo; bloodiest battles. Decades earlier, American Indians departed from Chattanooga&rsquo;s Ross&rsquo;s Landing and thus began the Cherokees departure west, known as the Trail of Tears. This historic land now serves as a go-to destination, ripe with sites of antiquity, outdoor adventures, and cultural offerings perfectly tailored for a family getaway or romantic weekend.<br />\n	Any good Chattanooga tour guide will suggest you try a piece of everything this southern city has to offer, but it&rsquo;s not such an easy feat. The mountainous lookout points, old-fashioned train rides, military roots, and performing arts offerings create a deeply historic city thrust into today&rsquo;s world with grace, beauty, and a neighborhood-like comfort.&nbsp;</p>\n', 1, 0, 220, '35.07', '-85.26', 'chattanooga', 0, 1),
