(6330, 2142, 'Vina del Mar', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	Known as the &ldquo;Garden City,&rdquo; Vi&ntilde;a del Mar is Chile&rsquo;s unofficial touristic capital with luxurious beaches and a lovely Mediterranean climate that supports bounteous greenery. Located close to Santiago, Vi&ntilde;a del Mar can be a fantastic day trip or a weeklong excursion, drawing in tourists from all over the world.<br />\n	A Vi&ntilde;a del Mar tour guide will recommend a traditional horse carriage ride to imbibe the impressive combination of traditional and modern architecture that blend seamlessly in this beach town. With incredible hotels, gourmet restaurants and the Vi&ntilde;a del Mar Casino, there is a fantastic assortment of places to stay and enjoy the comfort of the city. While there, visit Vergara Pier and the Flower Clock, some of Vi&ntilde;a del Mar&rsquo;s most famous landmarks amongst palaces, museums and parks to choose from. Enjoy the local criollo cuisine, featuring a bounty of fresh Chilean seafood alongside a glass of wine from a local vineyard. The city marks the end of summer with the International song Festival held at Quinta Vergara showcasing Latin and European artists.&nbsp; Vin&ntilde;a del Mar offers Chilean visitors history, culture, food, and beautiful sights, creating one of Chile&rsquo;s best cities to visit.</p>\n', 1, 0, 43, '-33.01', '-71.55', 'vina-del-mar', 0, 1),
(6331, 2142, 'Valparaiso', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	Valparaiso, called the &ldquo;Jewel of the Pacific,&rdquo; is a beautiful seaport on the western coast of Chile. Located northwest of the capital Santiago, Valparaiso boasts natural beauty and a mild Mediterranean climate making it an all time favourite with tourists.<br />\n	A rich history contributing to incredible historic landmarks and architecture has resulted in making Valparaiso a UNESCO World Heritage Site in 2003.&nbsp; Your Valparaiso tour guide will encourage you to walk through the city&rsquo;s cobblestone streets to admire the different architectural styles and colourful buildings as well as its renowned street art that give the city its&rsquo; unique bohemian character. The city&rsquo;s high incline cable cars, named as one of the world&rsquo;s &ldquo;100 most endangered historical treasures&rdquo; by the World Monument Fund in 1998 offer up a fantastic city views as also a practical way to get around town. Be sure to check out famous sites including the Iglesia de la Matriz, Plaza Sotomayor, Pablo Neruda&rsquo;s house, el Museo a Cielo Abierto, and the Plaza An&iacute;bal Pinto. The beautiful, historic Valparaiso offers these fascinating landmarks and much, much more.</p>\n', 1, 0, 43, '-33.04', '-71.64', 'valparaiso', 0, 1),
