(6340, 2147, 'Varna', 'Stalin', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	Reminding one of an amphitheatre, Varna is beautifully cushioned in a valley surrounded by the splendid greenery of vineyards and gardens. Start your day with a traditional breakfast of Banitsa, a delicious filo pastry filled with Bulgarian cheese with a dollop of Bulgarian yoghurt on the side. Your Varna Tourist guide will proudly showcase to you a city where historic churches and palaces blend easily with modern amenities. The most famous landmark in Varna would easily be the Cathedral of the Assumption of the Virgin, with its golden domes and intricate craved face shimmering in the sunlight. Explore the ruins of the Roman Baths reminding one of the wealth and the importance that this city once held and for a more comprehensive glimpse into history, visit the Archaeological Museum amongst others. Be entertained by the tricks of the highly agile dolphins at the Dolphinarium, the only one of its kind in the Balkan Peninsula. The stretches of Golden Sands are amongst the most spectacular beaches on the Bulgarian Black Sea Coastline with calm refreshing seas and densely populated forests running parallel. During the summer months be sure not to miss the Festival of Masked Dancers depicting traditional Bulgarian folklore or the vibrant nightlife where clubs and bars are open till the early hours of the morning.</p>\n', 1, 0, 21, '43.21', '27.90', 'varna', 0, 1),
