(6526, 2198, 'Wangdue', '', '<p class="fr-tag" style="text-align: justify;">This mystical conglomeration of white-washed temples and earthy woodwork homes on the edge of the Black Mountains of central Bhutan has long been a place shrouded in legend, known for its deep religiosity and authentic breed of Vajrayana Buddhism. It’s also the gateway to a beautiful corner of the Himalaya, awash with verdant valleys and sweeping, forest-clad hills.</p><p class="fr-tag" style="text-align: justify;"><span style="line-height: 16.7999992370605px; font-size: 1em; background-color: initial;">Most Wangdue tour guides will point first time visitors here straight to the Wangdue Dzong, sitting high on its perch in the Bhutanese mountains, laden with historic relics of the old Buddhist order. The road there will take travellers through some breath-taking scenery, encompassing sections of the rugged Phobjikha Valley, and offering up access to the exquisite Gangtey Monastery.</span></p><p class="fr-tag" style="text-align: justify;">The town of Wangdue itself is a charming affair of makeshift mountain homes that comes alive each year with the Black-neck Crane Festival, when locals celebrate the return of these elegant and endangered birds to their section of wild, Western Bhutan.</p>', 1, 0, 31, '27.48', '89.90', 'wangdue', 0, 1),
(6527, 2199, 'Olsztyn', 'Allenstein', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	Not many visitors venture this far east of northern Gdansk to realise the beauty of the undulating hills of Mazuria and Warmia. This is where the city of Olsztyn finds its home, perched neatly amidst the low-lying lakes and deep, verdant valleys of northern Poland. But, those who do decide to take the winding and untrodden paths to this medieval town will reap the rewards, because a lively old town and bustling centre await, pleasantly enjoying their undiscovered charm away from the clustering crowds of the country&rsquo;s better-known destinations.<br />\n	One of the great joys of this small city is exploring the web of cobbled streets and local caf&eacute;s of its old centre, and first time visitors should ask their Olsztyn tourist guide for walking routes that encompass the high gate to the north, the great gothic cathedral in the east and the bubbling main square of caf&eacute;s, pierogi joints and interesting little Polish beer houses.<br />\n	Olsztyn is also a perfect base for those interested in seeing the great lakes in the east of the country. These can be reached in around an hour and offer unparalleled recreation opportunities in the summer; from yachting across the waters to sunbathing in the Baltic sun.</p>\n', 1, 0, 172, '53.78', '20.49', 'olsztyn', 0, 1),
