(6532, 2201, 'Seattle', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	Seattle&rsquo;s pacific northwest location gives this metropolis a unique combination of exciting urban nightlife and breathtaking nature scarcely found in cities of its&rsquo; size. Its&rsquo; bustling distribution of libations, shops, and eateries give the city its&rsquo; spunk, while a dedication to culture and outdoor activities differentiate it from other cosmopolitan destinations.<br />\n	Its&rsquo; Discovery Park is perhaps the strongest indication of Seattle&rsquo;s commitment to nature, as a free, expansive space with hiking trails, beaches, sand dunes, and greenery. Along with guided kayaking, cycling, and sailing tours, staying indoors at all can be a difficult task. While a frequent melancholy drizzle often dampens the city, it rarely stops Seattle tour guides from making tourists appreciate this destination&rsquo;s worth.<br />\n	Still, enjoying the city&rsquo;s culture through one of the many museums and attractions is a perfect rain-day alternative; the Olympic Sculpture Garden and Seattle Art Museum house innovative creations, while the Seattle Aquarium and Museum of Flight are genre-specific must-sees for the interested traveller.&nbsp;</p>\n', 1, 0, 220, '47.62', '-122.35', 'seattle', 0, 1),
