(6578, 2207, 'Bruges', '', '<p>\n	One of the world&rsquo;s largest cities in the 11<sup>th</sup> century, the beautiful gothic city of Bruges epitomises picture postcard beauty. No wonder, it is a prize destination for tourists who throng the city during the summer months to admire its cobbled alleyways, century old houses and churches linked by market squares and arterial canals. &nbsp;Almost immaculately preserved, the City Centre is a good place to start where the medieval Belfry Tower stands tall and erect; climb the 366 steps for the most spectacular view of the St Salvator Cathedral and the Prinsenhof Castle looming large against the surrounding city. Take a boat trip along the Dijver Canal and witness first- hand the beauty of the medieval styled houses. Your Bruges tour guide will proudly show the exhibit of Michelangelo&rsquo;s magnificent sculpture- Madonna and Child, one of the few of his works outside Italy displayed in the ornately carved and decorated Church of our Lady. Walk through The Old Fish Market towards the Koningin Astrid Park to enjoy its tranquillity and well- manicured gardens. The quintessential tourist town, Bruges has fabulous restaurants; why not enjoy a seafood platter and one of the many desserts that are enriched with delicious Belgium chocolate.</p>\n', 1, 0, 19, '51.22', '3.23', 'bruges', 0, 1),
