(6816, 2233, 'Xian', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	Everyone from the conquering Zhou to the formidable Qin, the imperial Sui and the ancient Han came, saw, and occupied this aged city in the heart of the Guanzhong Plains. Some elevated it as the capital of China, nurturing a culture of innovation and enterprise, and some raised great monuments. Others brought only ruin and strife. Throughout this long historical narrative however, Xian has accumulated one of the richest arrays of sights in all of China, making it a veritable must for anyone travelling through this section of the north.<br />\n	There&rsquo;s perhaps little use in quizzing your Xian tour guide on the points of interest though, for they are so multitudinous that the list may even run longer than the great fourteen kilometre city wall that rings Xian itself. Yet, be sure to tick off the great Goose Pagoda, and the enthralling Forest of Steles. Then of course there&rsquo;s the Qinshihuang Mausoleum that pulls in excess of two million visitors a year, all eager to witness the formidable array of soldiers and horse that form the famous terracotta army!</p>\n', 1, 0, 45, '34.27', '108.90', 'xian', 0, 1),
