(6848, 2265, 'Lijiang', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	Considered one of the most beautiful ancient cities in China, Lijiang is located in the Yunnan province near Tibet.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	Three of the ancient districts of this small city are UNESCO World Heritage sites. With a history stretching way back to the late Song Dynasty of China, Lijiang has more than its fair share of interesting historical sites including the Old Town, where a nightly bonfire is held at 7pm, and the Mu Palace complete with Daoist temple. The mighty Yangtze River passes through Lijiang , overlooked by the famous Jade Dragon, or &lsquo;Yulong&rsquo;, Snow Mountains. You can explore the mountains by hiring a mule, ambitiously hiking to the top or more commonly, paying for a cable car. The view of the mountain massif from the gardens of the Black Dragon Pool is considered one of the most stunning views in all of China.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	&nbsp;Lijiang travel guides are available to show you around this gentle city, but don&rsquo;t be afraid to ask for help; the local culture of Lijiang is a joy and its people among the friendliest in Asia.&nbsp;</p>\n', 1, 0, 45, '26.53', '100.14', 'lijiang', 0, 1),
