(6951, 2314, 'Manaslu', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\n	As the eighth highest mountain in the world, Manaslu is best known for its&rsquo; hiking circuit. With lodges and sights along the trail, trekking Manaslu is far more than just a climb. Side trips to the peaceful, vegetarian Tsum Valley engage tourists in a lifestyle void of any violence or cruelty, while stops in local villages naturally teach visitors the intricacies of Nepal&rsquo;s Buddhist perspective and South Asian cuisine. While the hikes can be personalized to the skill of the climber, it is the cultural insight and local explorations that make Manaslu a journey like no other.<br />\n	Still, this adventure is not to be taken lightly. A good Manaslu tour guide will advise tourists of the dangers related to extreme altitude change. Preparing for this reality by staying hydrated and avoiding rapid ascents are must-do tasks for fully enjoying this eye-opening experience.&nbsp; So if the adventurer within you is screaming for a release, a trip to Manaslu might be just the outlet!</p>\n', 1, 0, 161, '28.33', '84.33', 'manaslu', 0, 1),
