(7541, 2313, 'Mustang', '', '<p class="fr-tag" style="text-align: justify;">Situated high on the cusp of the Tibetan plateau, this wild and largely untrodden region of Nepal remains a veritable gem for adventure travellers and the intrepid. Perhaps most notably, Mustang is famed as one of the trekking gateways to the mighty Annapurna Range, allowing access to some of the most coveted trails in the entire Himalaya.</p><p class="fr-tag" style="text-align: justify;">While hiking is the major draw here, your Mustang tour guide will tell you there is yet more to be experienced in these hills. Between the windswept ridges of dusty rock, the winding water channels of the lower district and the sweeping valleys of apple orchards, guests can seek out spots like the ancient city of Lo Manthang or the revered Hindu pilgrimage site of Muktinath. </p><p class="fr-tag" style="text-align: justify;">And once you’re done exploring the mystical side of the high valleys, why not settle in for a spot of Dal Bhat Tarkari lentil rice, or a taste of Mustang’s famous Marpha brandy as you mingle with the friendly locals in the former Kingdom of Lo.</p>', 1, 0, 161, '29.05', '83.55', 'mustang', 0, 1),
